findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges to change various parameters and settings, including tax and liquidity fees, maximum transaction amounts, marketing wallets, Uniswap router and pair, and more. The owner can also exclude from and include in autoliquidity, disable and enable swap and liquify, lock and unlock, which could be used to retake privileges even after ownership renouncement.

findings.title: DoS with block gas limit
findings.description: The contract may be vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) attacks due to block gas limit.

findings.title: Out of gas
findings.description: The functions includeInReward() and _getCurrentSupply() may be aborted with OUT_OF_GAS exception if there is a long excluded addresses list.
